If you do not reduce social subsidies or state operating expenses, you have to raise taxes.
To all to whom the left added now: firefighters, teachers, farmers.
And later, his children too.
People don’t have to worry about income or sickness subsidies, they will receive them. 1.800 million disappeared from these accounts.
But the price to be paid will be the increase in public debt; next year there will be only 163,000 million missing in the treasury, but more.
Despite Minister Janota’s effort, the debt will continue to rise alongside interest expenditures.
The state will need money to cover them and will no longer come with slightly increasing VAT or reducing maternity allowances, as the government did in its anti-deficit package.
Due to the dislocations of money for the benefit of some groups of voters, next year there will also be five billion to finish the construction of highways and railways.
These are, above all, the sectors in which the tender has already been held and where the construction process has already begun, whose projects cannot be changed and neither can its price be reduced.
