Nearly three billion were obtained from the budget to grant various compensation to victims of communism and crime, or to litigation expenses, including in construction savings.
It is unclear whether the state will need such funds.
It's a lottery.
If we lose any international litigation, we may have to pay for it, says Janota.
Afterwards, the Minister will have to save money inside the spring or, in the worst case, use the government budget reserve.
There are also a hundred million left for the Státní pokladna (State Box) project, whose price is two billion and which has already been started. It should allow online monitoring of what the various authorities are spending.
The first stage starts in January.
If the finance minister does not find the money elsewhere, the project will have to stop and sanctions will arrive, Janota warns.
