Experts hope that from next year more than 80 percent of young parents will let their babies vaccinate against pneumococcus.
The pneumococal vaccine is a big change also because as the first vaccination in children is covered by health companies, not by the state.
Insurance companies should spend more money on prophylaxis, to save later on treatment, explains Cabrnochová.
Doctors will have to buy the vaccines for themselves.
However, pediatricians are concerned about the purchase of vaccines.
Previously, vaccines had to be purchased by insurance companies and distributed to doctors, just like when the state gives them other vaccines.
Some MPs were afraid, however, that insurance companies could “take the money out of health insurance.”
Doctors will have to buy the vaccines and wait until they are paid for by the insurance companies.
It is estimated that pediatricians will invest in vaccines 40 thousand a month, which is a remarkable sum.
It won't be easy, says Cabrnochová.
