Marines among the 6,000 who place crowns on Arlington's graves
Pfc. De'Angello Robinson, 19, traveled seven hours by bus to place a single crown on the grave of a soldier he had never met.
For him and the other Marines who traveled from Camp Johnson in Jacksonville, N.C., to Arlington National Cemetery to decorate graves, it was a day to pay tribute to men and women who were once standing in their boots.
In a few months, from where we are being shipped, these could be us, Robinson said of the fallen soldiers.
