The Stuttgart 21 Dimension is not placed at all high enough.
For the supporters of the project it is simply and plainly "the new heart of Europe".
The law is. S21 is much more than the reduction of a railway station, more than a monstrous construction project, which will precipitate into the capital of the Banden-Württemberga region a decade of chaos from irremediable construction sites.
Stuttgart 21 emerged from the spirit of the 1980s.
Terminals with rails, which end up in the middle of the city, were considered at that time engineering fossils of the nineteenth century, which acted as brakes of a modern rail traffic, since in the past a huge amount of time was needed to hook the locomotives back forward.
Roll, stop dry continue the journey; but so it must be done.
And that is why the terminals had to disappear: in Frankfurt and Munich.
And in Stuttgart: a passage station, which is approximately halfway along the path of the trans-European operating lines between Paris and Budapest/Bratislava; hence the slogan "Heart of Europe".
The S21 will really be initiated, even though the visions of the 80’s are no longer compatible with reality.
Even the most ambitious designers have known that in the Hessian and Bavarian capitals it is almost unpayable to implement the reduction.
