The passage station and the road support are designed for the transport of people, which was attributed to the enormous growth typical of the 1980’s.
At that time there was no competition from low-cost flights.
But modern transport policy must first be addressed in strengthening freight transport, since rail transport is considerably greener than that carried out by trucks on the roads.
